Operatives of the Anti-Kidnapping Unit of the Rivers State Police Command has recovered decomposed corpses of three students of the University of Port Harcourt, who were kidnapped and killed at Etoo forest in Eleme local government area of Rivers State. The three students, two males, Nelson Nwafor and Fortune Obimba, as well as a female, Joy Adoki, a four hundred level student, were kidnapped near the University campus at Choba. The Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) in the state, Nnamdi Omoni, who led newsmen into the thick Etoo forest, said three suspects has been arrested in connection to the kidnap and murder. Omoni, a Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP), said investigations continue to track down other members of the gang. Speaking to newsmen, one of the suspects, who led the Police to the forest where the corpses were exumed, Friday Akpan, said a member of the gang, identified as Bright kidnapped the deceased trio. Akpan stated that Bright alleged that be of the victims was owing him some money, adding that Bright claimed to be a soldier and ordered them to kill the victims. 